<span class="s1">&lt;/table&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The joystick module manages the joystick devices on a computer.</span>
<span class="s0">Joystick devices include trackballs and video-game-style</span>
<span class="s0">gamepads, and the module allows the use of multiple buttons and </span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">hats</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">.</span>
<span class="s0">Computers may manage multiple joysticks at a time.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Each instance of the Joystick class represents one gaming device plugged</span>
<span class="s0">into the computer. If a gaming pad has multiple joysticks on it, then the</span>
<span class="s0">joystick object can actually represent multiple joysticks on that single</span>
<span class="s0">game device.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">For a quick way to initialise the joystick module and get a list of Joystick instances</span>
<span class="s0">use the following code:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight-default notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">joystick</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">init</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;p&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">joysticks</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;o&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">=</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; <span class="s1">&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The following event types will be generated by the joysticks</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight-default notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">JOYAXISMOTION</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">JOYBALLMOTION</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">JOYBUTTONDOWN</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">JOYBUTTONUP</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">JOYHATMOTION</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">And in pygame 2, which supports hotplugging:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight-default notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">JOYDEVICEADDED</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;n&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">JOYDEVICEREMOVED</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Note that in pygame 2, joysticks events use a unique </span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">instance ID</span><span class="s4">&amp;quot;</span><span class="s0">. The device index</span>
<span class="s0">passed in the constructor to a Joystick object is not unique after devices have</span>
<span class="s0">been added and removed. You must call </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.joystick.Joystick.get_instance_id&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.joystick.Joystick.get_instance_id&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Joystick.get_instance_id()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">to find</span>
<span class="s0">the instance ID that was assigned to a Joystick on opening.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The event queue needs to be pumped frequently for some of the methods to work.</span>
<span class="s0">So call one of pygame.event.get, pygame.event.wait, or pygame.event.pump regularly.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Create a new joystick to access a physical device. The id argument must be a</span>
<span class="s0">value from </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">0</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">to </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.joystick.get_count()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">-</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Joysticks are initialised on creation and are shut down when deallocated.</span>
<span class="s0">Once the device is initialized the pygame event queue will start receiving</span>
<span class="s0">events about its input.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

Gamepad devices</span>
<span class="s0">will usually be </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">-1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">0</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, or </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">with no values in between. <span class="s0">analog joystick axes will not always use the full </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">-1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">to </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">range,</span>
<span class="s0">and the centered value will be some area around </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">0</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Start a rumble effect on the joystick, with the specified strength ranging</span>
<span class="s0">from 0 to 1. Duration is length of the effect, in ms. Setting the duration</span>
<span class="s0">to 0 will play the effect until another one overwrites it or</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.joystick.Joystick.stop_rumble&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.joystick.Joystick.stop_rumble&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Joystick.stop_rumble()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">is called. If an effect is already</span>
<span class="s0">playing, then it will be overwritten.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
